## Public Constructors

### EPCDynamicLibrarySearchGenerator() {#af9de54b6e1a0704874430d55c7a5b069}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>llvm::orc::EPCDynamicLibrarySearchGenerator::EPCDynamicLibrarySearchGenerator (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/executionsession">ExecutionSession</a> &amp; ES, <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/orc/tpctypes/#a791ec0843cc10da4c64ae6d79f8381d8">tpctypes::DylibHandle</a> H, <a href="#a451bf5760fcb04c7a63fcbe745ac7b17">SymbolPredicate</a> Allow=<a href="#a451bf5760fcb04c7a63fcbe745ac7b17">SymbolPredicate</a>(), <a href="#ac870c7932e4bf13d01b19e0e611d96a0">AddAbsoluteSymbolsFn</a> AddAbsoluteSymbols=nullptr)</>}
  labels = {["inline"]}>
Create a <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/dynamiclibrarysearchgenerator">DynamicLibrarySearchGenerator</a> that searches for symbols in the library with the given handle.

If the Allow predicate is given then only symbols matching the predicate will be searched for. If the predicate is not given then all symbols will be searched for.

If <code>AddAbsoluteSymbols</code> is provided, it is used to add the symbols to the <code><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a></code>; otherwise it uses JD.define(absoluteSymbols(...)).

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/executionengine/include/llvm/executionengine/orc/epcdynamiclibrarysearchgenerator-h/#l00039">39</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/executionengine/include/llvm/executionengine/orc/epcdynamiclibrarysearchgenerator-h">EPCDynamicLibrarySearchGenerator.h</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

</SectionDefinition>

## Public Member Functions

### tryToGenerate() {#acd769134fc784667d68b675ee79b609d}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>Error llvm::orc::EPCDynamicLibrarySearchGenerator::tryToGenerate (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/lookupstate">LookupState</a> &amp; LS, <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/orc/#ac17672ae6b70c781cc77713e88d698eb">LookupKind</a> K, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a> &amp; JD, <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/orc/#a7cb1d8cb0ab2329f032d69d79498c81d">JITDylibLookupFlags</a> JDLookupFlags, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/symbollookupset">SymbolLookupSet</a> &amp; LookupSet)</>}
  labels = {["virtual"]}>
DefinitionGenerators should override this method to insert new definitions into the parent <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a>.

K specifies the kind of this lookup. JD specifies the target <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/jitdylib">JITDylib</a> being searched, and JDLookupFlags specifies whether the search should match against hidden symbols. Finally, Symbols describes the set of unresolved symbols and their associated lookup flags.

### Load() {#a0be4b6ee27375703c0be30f0b730d0ba}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>Expected&lt; std::unique&#95;ptr&lt; EPCDynamicLibrarySearchGenerator &gt; &gt; llvm::orc::EPCDynamicLibrarySearchGenerator::Load (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/executionsession">ExecutionSession</a> &amp; ES, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> char &#42; LibraryPath, <a href="#a451bf5760fcb04c7a63fcbe745ac7b17">SymbolPredicate</a> Allow=<a href="#a451bf5760fcb04c7a63fcbe745ac7b17">SymbolPredicate</a>(), <a href="#ac870c7932e4bf13d01b19e0e611d96a0">AddAbsoluteSymbolsFn</a> AddAbsoluteSymbols=nullptr)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
Permanently loads the library at the given path and, on success, returns a <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/orc/dynamiclibrarysearchgenerator">DynamicLibrarySearchGenerator</a> that will search it for symbol definitions in the library.

On failure returns the reason the library failed to load.
